{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013s9miCc4dKEPPBXrUXSu4m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All sprint contract criteria pass. Here's the summary:\n\n## What changed\n\n**Root cause (from eval):** `new Response(stream, { headers })` in Next.js App Router doesn't flush HTTP status/headers until the first byte of the body is written. With ClickHouse down or an empty database, the interval never enqueued anything, so the client hung forever.\n\n**Fix — `src/app/api/live/route.ts` (one line added):**\n```typescript\nstart(controller) {\n  // Flush headers immediately on connect — SSE clients ignore \":\" comments\n  controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(\":\\n\\n\"));\n\n  intervalId = setInterval(async () => { ... }, 1000);\n}\n```\n\n**Test updates — `src/app/api/live/__tests__/route.test.ts`:**\n- Added new test: \"immediately enqueues a keep-alive SSE comment on connect before any timer fires\"\n- Updated 2 existing tests to consume the keep-alive chunk before asserting on `data:` lines (factual corrections — the old assertions became impossible once a chunk is always enqueued first)\n\n## Results\n\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| `pnpm test` | 260 passed, 25 skipped, 0 failures |\n| `pnpm lint` | exit 0 (4 pre-existing warnings, 0 new) |\n| `pnpm typecheck` | exit 0 |\n| `pnpm build` | exit 0, `ƒ /api/live` listed |\n| HTTP check (`GET /api/live`) | `200 OK`, `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, headers flushed immediately even without ClickHouse |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1147,"cache_read_input_tokens":50218,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1147},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce077e65-4534-4c39-a351-8424f9104da0","uuid":"b42678ed-21e3-4951-ba10-6b250